cities.Name: Zostel Aurangabad
cities.Description: The old forts, age-old eateries, and museums narrate their own tales. The distinctive scent of naan qualia tingles both your nose and taste buds. And with gorgeous sunsets over the sky like a giant painting, Aurangabad breaks all stereotypes one wonder at a time. Welcome to a city with rich heritage, stupendous monuments, and world-famous caves.

stays.staysDescription: Stay with us at Zostel Aurangabad, the only backpacker hostel of Aurangabad. Centrally-located, fun, social and affordable place to hang out with travellers from around the world.

roomDetails.name: Zostel Aurangabad
roomDetails.description: Zostel Aurangabad, the liveliest backpacker hostel in Aurangabad, is located just 7 km from the Aurangabad Airport and 3.4 km from Aurangabad Railway station. Don’t mistake Aurangabad to be just the land of Ajanta & Ellora Caves and explore the cultural heritage it holds so dearly. Besides this, there are old forts and more for the history lovers, art galleries and museums for the art lovers and the endless Food scene for the foodies! Take a walk at Siddarth Garden while the sun sets and you will realise you have found a place you will never want to leave. Come and stay at our cosy hostel and experience Aurangabad like a local!

Feel free to lounge around in our AC common room during the days while sharing your travel stories with fellow backpackers on our rooftop lounging area till late into the night. If the traveller in you is calling out, we’ll hear it well. Each day in Zostel Bangalore is happening, complete with doses of laughter and experiences. Chill out with the coolest set of people from around the world and travel without hassle. Before your mischievous mind starts wandering far, let us put one thing real straight - we take the comfort of each and every traveller very seriously.

roomDetails.name: Zostel Barot (Rajgundha)
roomDetails.description: Resting secluded in the snow-white meadows of the Barot Valley of Himachal, Zostel Rajgundha is the perfect rejuvenation haven for digital nomads and anyone who loves a self-contained getaway in the mountains. With a dedicated collaboration area and a workspace for you to create, collaborate, and explore, the hostel teems with spirited energy in a tranquil landscape. Begin your morning with a hearty breakfast at the in-house café and then fill your day with board games, Yoga, dynamic work sessions, reading, and lots of holiday goodness. And when the sun goes down painting the skies crimson and gold, turn the speaker on with some soft songs, light up the bonfire, and dance the starry night away with your friends. Come, disengage from the everyday city life and delve into solitude, nature, and lots of snow!

cities.Description: About Perched up above most of India, in the Himalayas bordering Tibet, Chitkul is the kind of beauty that leaves you thoroughly awe-struck and grasping for more. The mountains here seem mightier than most other places, the air seems quieter, and life much slower. Coloured pink with Buckwheat blooms in Spring, white with thick blankets of snow in winters.

roomDetails.name: Zostel Chitkul
roomDetails.description: The last village on the Indo-Tibet border, Chitkul, is truly one of the hidden gems of India. The village, at first glance will give you a feeling of time travel, way back into the past. The main attraction in Zostel Chitkul offers you a panoramic view of the Himalayan range on one side, dense trees on the other, and the sparkling ever-gushing river Baspa flowing behind the hostel. Speaking of its beauty, each sight is a magnificent sight to behold. No wonder, Chitkul is any photography lover’s haven.

Also named ‘Scotland of India’, Coorg attracts travelers from all over the world with its verdant landscapes. A carpet of coffee plantations and a blanket of peace covers the entire town, along with hot spices and a chilly breeze all around the year. The winding roads and the paths untraveled call out to the adventurous souls too but come here to rejuvenate every sense in your body and you will leave with an unprecedented calm and a resolve to come back! Zostel Coorg is tucked away in the greenest lands of the town. With a variety of dormitories, we have plenty of places where travelers can mingle apart from the cozy common room and the multi-cuisine cafe. For the more adventure-loving of the lot, we have tents for you to camp with wilderness around you.

cities.Name: Zostel Delhi
cities.Description: A little goes a long way when it comes to exploring Delhi and one thing that’s for sure is that you won’t have to travel too far to explore its absolute best. The narrow lanes of Old Delhi overflooded with people tantalise you with the most palatable street food, whereas the quiet streets of Central & Southern Delhi house monuments that speak of the royal Mughal dynasty galore. With a kickass nightlife, impressive food scene, and an arena of places to explore, shop, and live

stays.staysDescription: Stay at Zostel Delhi - THE most centrally located, top-ranked backpacker hostel of Delhi. Direct airport metro and walking distance to train station, Connaught Place and Old Delhi.

roomDetails.name: Zostel Delhi
roomDetails.description: Zostel Delhi is THE most centrally located, top-ranked backpacker hostel in Delhi. Our hostel is close to the direct airport metro and a short walk away from the train station, Connaught Place and Old Delhi. From the narrowest lanes with small shops to swanky malls; from roadside chaat stalls to the most expensive restaurants; with a charm that combines the eras of ancient India, the Mughals, the British, and the post-independence India, Delhi has stood witness to changes since time immemorial. Delhi has been a stirring pot of Indian cultures, as is befitting to a capital city. Right in its heart lies the backpacking hub of Paharganj, which might seem a bit sleepy and noisy in the day but comes alive, larger than life, in the night. Zostel Delhi, on a busy street of Paharganj, is often the first stop for International travellers before embarking to other destinations in India. One visit to Delhi is enough to lose one’s heart to it forever.

stays.staysDescription: Set in Shimla in the Himachal Pradesh region, Zostel Homes Theog (Shimla) offers accommodation with free private parking. A buffet breakfast is available every morning at the homestay. Guests can also relax in the shared lounge area.

cities.Name: Bir
cities.Description: Zostel Plus Bir in Bīr provides adults-only accommodation with a restaurant, a shared lounge and a garden.

stays.staysDescription: Zostel Wayanad is a quaint backpacking hostel located amidst sprawling tea plantations right at the base of the famous Chembra Peak. We offer an ideal setting for the young social travellers and digital nomads to explore Wayanad.

A luxe villa nestled in 1000 acres of a private estate, with plush private rooms, natural bathrooms, and exclusive access to nearby waterfalls, hiking trails, and more. This villa is bookable only on a full-house basis.

Located on the banks of the laidback Karapuzha dam, this homestay is perfect for a close-knit rendezvous with the goodness of nature. It features vast balconies, a verdant lawn and bonfire area, indoor games, and hill views with a charming sunset.
Located in Thirunelly, Zostel Homes Wayanad offers a unique stay experience, brimming with unimaginable greenery and wilderness all around.
